Package ca.mcgill.ecse211.project

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ColorDetector
    Class that has a reference to the colour light sensor to calibrate the initial colours and then detect which colours it is using the mean and standard deviation for initial colours
    LightPoller
    The LightPoller class has access to a lightsensor sample provider and is able to poll the current colour value.
    Main
    Main class is the main entry point of the robot.
    Movement
    The Movement class is the only class that has access to the motors and performs all movement.
    Odometer
    Odometer Class keeps track of current x, y position and theta orientation.
    Point
    s Represents a coordinate point on the competition map grid.
    Region
    Represents a region on the competition map grid, delimited by its lower-left and upper-right corners (inclusive).
    Resources
    This class is used to define static resources in one place for easy access and to avoid cluttering the rest of the codebase.
    Robot
    Static class that coordinates all actions by using the other resources.
    UltrasonicSensor
    Class that performs all the ultrasonic behaviour:
    Wifi
    Pseudo wifi class used in debugging and prior to the implementation of the wifi downloading
